enFromWeb?topicID=332.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Time for a reality check. PLEASE READ!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hey all. Just got back from Broken Bow and was very pumped after a GREAT 2 days of intensive training. I loved the office and they loved me! After a 4 hour drive home I was all set to log on AC and take a look at the new patch ... until I ran across a story on Lum the Mad's site about an EQ gamer. Or should I say a former EQ gamer. It appears that this very young lady of only 18 years took her own life last Saturday. She had a lot of things going against her in life and was in a pretty desperate situation but her one release and escape from all the demons of everyday life was through her online life and friends. Apparently, part of that was denied her due to a misunderstanding or someones attempt to cause her problems in game. Regardless, in her very scared and confused mind this contributed to the last straw and her last desperate act on this earth was to take her own life with a handgun. <br>
<br>
I'm a very happy-go-lucky, fly by the seat of my pants kind of guy but I can be intense at times ... but I wasn't always like this. In 1992 my wife of 7 years took her own life. I have lived through a loved ones suicide and thought that maybe I should join her. But through friends, family and lots of TLC and counseling I made it through what was probably the blackest moment in my young life.<br>
<br>
I know what it is like to have friends by your side as well as only having your online friends care about you. My heart goes out to this young lady and the 2 year old child that will never get a chance to grow up with Mommy. Anyway, I guess that this rambling has a point and I had better get to it. You, my online friends, are family to me. Sure we have never met but we have shared so much through our talks that you are a part of my life. I am here for anyone of you at any time. Me, Rick Lange. I know we all have our own lives but i am always here to talk online, by email or on the phone. I just wanted you all to know that and it is NO trouble at all. I care about each and everyone of you. Maybe you don't have a life or death situation but even a friendly voice can sometimes help. My work number is 1-800-588-0885. Please call me or even better email me at work and I will give you my home email and telephone number. I would never want any of you to ever think you were alone and had no one to turn to.<br>
<br>
Ok, that took a lot out of me. See you all soon!<br>
<br>
Rick</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Wamba</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>11/15/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>2:57:36 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=332.topic&index=1><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">reply</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I get my on-line enjoyment by being a buffoon, but that doesn't mean that I don't recognize a class act when I see one.<br>
